  </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thoughts on EQ2</span><hr size=1> I haven't read all the details on item decay for EQ2, but I could see them having things &quot;break&quot; but be fixable, maybe through tradeskills.  <br>
<br>
I also seem to remember them saying that the chance of something breaking was related to whether or not you were a high enough level to use the item, so it almost seemed like item decay was a form of anti-twinking.  Maybe if you're at or above the &quot;recommended level&quot; for the item it won't decay. <p><BR>
