<br>
What you're referring to was mentioned in the article I referenced yesterday, but I can't find it today.  Anyway, there won't be stats to be figured at 1st level.  You won't choose your players skills.  They intend for there to be only three attributes, Skill, knowledge, and arts.<br>
<br>
Knowledge, I think, is what will affect item decay.  I might be wrong though.  They mentioned it specifically and said that a low level player would be able to USE high end gear, but they would be MUCH more likely to break it than a high level player.<br>
<br>
Hopefully, they will also code in some sort of EPIC flag to make items that do NOT decay, as some things you just shouldn't have to worry about.<br>
<br>
-Aragir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uartanor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>artanor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/23/02 7:58:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16068.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: item decay and skills</span><hr size=1> I very much doubt that you Breastplate could break unless you neglect it or fighting a mob that is too powerfull for it to withstand against. I would asume that your Uber Vex-Thal (or wherever) class  breastplate will stand up to lesser mobs without trouble provided it was cared for. And should it break then your spare in the bank will not have rotted at all since it hasnt been used. I am sure you will have greased it before putting it in safe keeping :-). Anyway Us Smiths could do with some steady work.<br>
